# .pii-denylist — template (ADR-0055)
#
# Copy to `.pii-denylist` (gitignored) and fill with the REAL literals that
# must never enter the public repo, one per line. scripts/pii-scan.sh matches
# these case-insensitively as fixed strings and BLOCKS on any hit — in tracked
# files, staged changes, and commit messages. Matches are always redacted in
# output (printed as `[denylist#<sha8>] file:line`) so neither a local hook nor
# a public CI log ever echoes the string itself.
#
# In CI the real list lives in the `PII_DENYLIST` repo secret (Settings →
# Secrets and variables → Actions), one entry per line, materialized into
# `.pii-denylist` for the run. Keep this file and the secret in sync.
#
# Rules:
#   * Blank lines and lines starting with `#` are ignored.
#   * Fixed strings, not regexes. Case-insensitive.
#   * NEVER commit the filled-in `.pii-denylist` — it is gitignored for a reason.
#
# What belongs here (examples of CATEGORIES — do NOT put real values in THIS
# template file; it is tracked and public):
#   - Real business / store names that appear as connection ids or sample data.
#   - The maintainer's real personal email address.
#   - The maintainer's real full name, if it should not be in the public repo.
#   - The maintainer's real OS username (as it appears in machine paths).
#   - Any real hostname / cluster id that identifies a production system.
#
# Example lines (illustrative placeholders — replace, do not keep):
# AcmeMegaStore
# jane.doe@somecorp.co.jp
# Jane Doe
# jdoe
